<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Bebeto May Join MetroStars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) -- Former Brazilian World Cup star  
Bebeto might be headed to Major League Soccer's New York-New Jersey 
MetroStars, his agent said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Bebeto is keen to go,'' agent Leo Rabello said. ``I am  
negotiating with a MetroStars representative and he may join them 
in July after the Rio state soccer championship ends.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rabello said the 35-year-old forward wants a two-year contract.  
Under MLS' single-entity ownership structure, all players sign 
contracts with the league, which then assigns them to teams. 
</P>
<P>
	``As much as I'd like to say that a player of Bebeto's stature  
is signed and coming to MLS, there are no official negotiations 
that I know of at the present time,'' league spokesman Dan 
Courtemanche said. ``Certainly someone from the MetroStars could 
have talked to Bebeto. Those discussions happen all the time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bebeto has been booed by some fans of Botafogo, which has  
struggled in this year's state championships. But the team is doing 
far better in the Brazilian Cup and needs just a tie with Atletico 
Parana on Wednesday to advance to the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
	Bebeto was quoted as saying Monday that he had received an  
``excellent offer'' from the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am going to think about it calmly, but first I want to give  
Botafogo the Brazil Cup,'' he told the Jornal Do Brasil. 
</P>
<P>
	Bebeto played for Brazil in the last three World Cups.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
