<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Queen Amidala Missed 1st Star Wars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Natalie Portman was far from a ``Star Wars'' fan  
when she landed the role of Queen Amidala in the latest 
installment. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was born in Israel and I lived there for my first three  
years,'' said the 17-year-old Long Islander. ``By the time I got to 
the United States, all the films had already come out. So I missed 
it the first time around.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Portman plays a queen who resists invasion of her country in  
``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace.'' 
</P>
<P>
	She said Sunday that she plays a ``strong female character  
that's really good for girls. She has this unembarrassed 
idealism.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Portman also appeared in ``The Professional.''  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
