<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mrs. Clinton Plans Trip to Ireland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Hillary Rodham Clinton is flying to Ireland to  
inaugurate a university lecture series Wednesday about the 
millennium and then travel to Belfast and London. 
</P>
<P>
	The first lady is scheduled to speak Wednesday at the National  
University of Ireland at Galway, celebrating its 150th anniversary, 
and will be made an honorary citizen of Galway. 
</P>
<P>
	Later in the day, Mrs. Clinton is to go to Belfast for the  
groundbreaking of a playground for children exposed to violence in 
Northern Ireland. She also plans to meet with women members of the 
Northern Ireland Assembly. 
</P>
<P>
	On Thursday, she is scheduled to address a Vital Voices  
Conference of women involved in efforts to curb tensions between 
Protestants and Catholics. Afterward, Mrs. Clinton plans to go to 
London to speak at a conference about human rights for children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
