<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Imaoka Retains Featherweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Takeo Imaoka of Japan defended his Orient-Pacific  
featherweight title Monday by knocking out Noel Pan of the 
Philippines in the eighth round of a scheduled 12-round title bout. 
</P>
<P>
	The knockout came at 2 minutes, 18 seconds of the eighth round.  
</P>
<P>
	Imaoka attacked Pan, No. 6-ranked Orient-Pacific contender, with  
straight rights from the fifth round and knocked him out in the 
eighth with a left hook to the chin. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Imaoka's fourth defense of the title he won from Samuel  
Duran of the Philippines in November 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Imaoka weighed 126 pounds and Pan weighed 125.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
