<HEADLINE> Shopper Jailed for Attacking Clerk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TROY, Mich. (AP) -- An angry Christmas shopper whose attack on a  
department store clerk was captured on video got 10 days in jail 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Miranda Smith, 21, also was fined $500, placed on probation for  
one year and ordered to attend an anger-management class. 
</P>
<P>
	She had pleaded guilty to assault and battery.  
</P>
<P>
	The Dec. 2 surveillance video from the Hudson's department store  
at Oakland Mall showed her step behind the sales counter, push the 
clerk, throw her to the ground and swing at her head. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said Ms. Smith had been frustrated by what she perceived  
as poor service. 
</P>
<P>
	The tape showed Ms. Smith had been waiting for help from a busy  
sales clerk. When she asked for a different size dress, the clerk 
rolled her eyes and another clerk laughed. Ms. Smith attacked the 
second clerk. 
</P>
<P>
	The victim, Marcia Temerowski, asked for $5,000 in restitution.  
The judge did not immediately decide on the request. 
</P>
</TEXT>
