<HEADLINE> Garciaparra Has 3 HRs, Drives in 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Nomar Garciaparra hit a pair of grand slams and a  
two-run homer, driving in 10 RBIs during Boston's game against 
Seattle on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Garciaparra, who hit his first home run of the season last  
Wednesday, hit his second career grand slam in the first inning off 
rookie Brett Hinchliffe, then hit another in the eighth off Eric 
Weaver for 12-3 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	The two-run homer came off Hinchliffe in the third inning.  
</P>
<P>
	Garciaparra, who hit a grand slam against the Mariners on Sept.  
2, 1998, also hit a solo homer in Sunday's 4-2 win over Anaheim. He 
hit 35 home runs last year and has five this season. 
</P>
<P>
	The 10 RBIs tied the Red Sox record, a mark last accomplished by  
Fred Lynn on June 18, 1975 at Detroit. 
</P>
<P>
	In his other at-bats, Garciaparra fouled out and walked.  
</P>
