<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Down in Early Trading / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stock prices fell in early trading Tuesday  
amid caution about current high price levels. The dollar was lower 
against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nikkei Stock Average fell 123.24 points, or 0.73 percent, to  
16,853.77 in the first 30 minutes of trading. On Monday, the 
average gained 30.49 points, or 0.18 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar was traded at 120.42 yen, down 0.44 yen from late in  
Tokyo on Monday and also below its level of 120.50 yen in New York. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, foreign and individual Japanese investors  
continued to buy stocks, but domestic institutional investors were 
selling on concerns the market may be rising too fast. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was down 10.59 points, or 0.77 percent, to 1,363.27. 
The TOPIX closed up 5.44 points, or 0.40 percent, Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency trading, the dollar fell on news late Monday that  
the Yugoslav army had announced a partial withdrawal of military 
and police forces in Kosovo. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 130.19 yen, up from  
129.38 yen late Friday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the 10-year Japanese government bond was unchanged  
from its Monday close of 1.335 percent, leaving its price at 104.13 
yen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
