<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Joan Kennedy Has Heart Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Joan Kennedy, the ex-wife of Sen. Edward M.  
Kennedy, suffered a mild heart attack and was being treated in a 
hospital Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Kennedy, 62, suffered the heart attack Friday, said her  
son, Rep. Patrick Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
	She was in fair condition Monday night Massachusetts General  
Hospital, a hospital spokeswoman said. She underwent an angiogram, 
a test in which doctors inject dye into the heart arteries to check 
for a slowing of the blood flow. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Kennedy was to undergo another series of diagnostic tests  
on Tuesday, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Kennedy, who was divorced from the senator in 1983, has  
described herself as a recovering alcoholic and has spent time in a 
number of rehabilitation programs following arrests for drunken 
driving. 
</P>
<P>
	Patrick Kennedy said in a statement that he spent Mother's Day  
weekend with his mother in the hospital and he expected his 
brother, Ted Kennedy Jr., and his sister, Kara Allen, to join them. 
Mrs. Kennedy is expected to stay in the hospital the rest of the 
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
