<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily ...day on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 


</P>
<P>
	Newmont Mining, down 1 7/8 at 20 7/8.  
</P>
<P>
	Meridian Gold, down 7/16 at 5 5/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold stocks fell as the price of gold continued to decline.  

</P>
<P>
	May Department Stores Co., down 5/8 at 44 3/8.  
</P>
<P>
	First-quarter earnings climbed more than 17 percent from a year  
ago, boosted by a surge in sales. The St. Louis-based retailer 
earned 34 cents a share, up from 29 cents a year ago and topping 
analysts' expectations by a penny. 

</P>
<P>
	MotivePower Industries, Inc., up 1 13/16 at 20 1/8.  
</P>
<P>
	Bay State Transit Services LLC, which is 75 percent owned by  
MotivePower subsidiary Boise Locomotive, has been selected by the 
Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority to negotiate a five-year 
contract for up to $175 million to provide rail equipment 
maintenance for MBTA's commuter rail line in Boston. 

</P>
<P>
	Lucent Technologies Inc. rose 1 1/16 to 58 13/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Lucent unveiled a single-chip system for Internet telephones.  
The company said the system reduces the electronics costs of 
Internet telephones by about 30 percent and decreases the number of 
semiconductor chips typically required for Internet telephones to 
one from five. 

</P>
<P>
	Unisource Worldwide Inc. rose 2 3/4 to 11 1/2.  
</P>
<P>
	Georgia Pacific fell 6 5/8 to 92.  
</P>
<P>
	Unisource, an Arizona electric service company, received an  
unsolicited proposal to be acquired by Georgia-Pacific Corp. for 
$12 a share in cash. In a press release Monday, Unisource said the 
offer has been approved by Georgia-Pacific's board and is not 
subject to Georgia-Pacific's securing financing. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
	Merisel Inc., up 5/8 at 2 13/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Merisel was one of only four distributors selected to  
participate in Compaq Computer Corp.'s North American Distributor 
Alliance Program. The new program slashed the number of Compaq 
distributors to 4 from about 40. 

</P>
<P>
	Zonagen Inc., down 9 at 10 13/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Schering-Plough, up 5/8 at 50 5/8 on the New York Stock Exchange.  
</P>
<P>
	The two drug companies agreed to forego a June Food and Drug  
Administration advisory panel review of a new drug application for 
Vasomax, Zonagen's oral treatment for erectile dysfunction. 

</P>
<P>
	Sport Chalet Inc., up 1 3/8 at 6 1/2.  
</P>
<P>
	The company signed an agreement with Global Sports Interactive  
to sell its merchandise online. 

</P>
