<HEADLINE>  Albania Sees New Refugee Influx </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KUKES, Albania (AP) -- A recent Serb offensive in southwest  
Kosovo has produced a new wave of refugees at the Albanian border 
and again strained the meager resources of this mountain town, a 
U.N. official said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Nearly 16,000 Kosovo refugees straggled across the border over  
the weekend, relaying tales of Serbs driving them out from the 
towns of Pec and Djakovica. And the influx was expected to 
continue. 
</P>
<P>
