	The UNHCR and other aid groups are trying to strike a balance  
between providing enough resources for all the new arrivals, and 
strongly encouraging the refugees to move south as soon as 
possible. 
</P>
<P>
	Kukes is simply not equipped to handle the population it has  
now, aid workers say. The town is also within range of Serb 
artillery, and the Yugoslav security forces have shelled some 
Albanian border regions in recent weeks. 
</P>
<P>
