of the remote northeast corner of the country, raising further 
security concerns. Already, there have been a number of problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Albanian boys stand by the side of the road and wave at the  
newly arrived refugees on the tractors, and as they pass, the 
youths snatch clothes, food, and other supplies that may have been 
dangling over the side of the slow-moving vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
	Aid groups fear such petty theft could increase frictions  
between refugees and Albanians. 
