<HEADLINE> Atlanta's Crawford Injured in Game 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Atlanta Hawks forward Chris Crawford sprained his  
right shoulder Monday night when he tumbled to the court after a 
tip-in during Game 2 of the first-round playoff series against 
Detroit. 
</P>
<P>
	Crawford scored the first six points for the Hawks, the last  
basket coming as he stretched out to tip in a missed shot by Mookie 
Blaylock with 9:08 remaining in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-9 forward stretched out to reach the ball and fell to  
the court afterwards, landing hard on his right shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Crawford was taken to the locker room for X-rays. He could not  
return to the game. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury further depleted the Hawks' depth. Crawford started  
the final 30 games of the regular season after LaPhonso Ellis was 
sidelined with a sports hernia. Forward Alan Henderson, still 
suffering double vision caused by a severe abrasion to his left 
eye, did not play in the first half Monday after managing only four 
minutes in Game 1. 
</P>
<P>
	Atlanta led the Eastern Conference series after a 90-70 victory  
Saturday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
