<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> `The Mummy' Takes In $44 Million / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``The Mummy'' burst into North American  
theaters with a record $43.4 million box office take, the largest 
nonsummer opening in movie history and ninth among the top 10 
all-time opening weekends. 
</P>
<P>
	The success of the Universal Pictures remake of the 1932 Boris  
Karloff classic even caught studio executives by surprise. 
Universal Studios president Ron Meyer had expected something around 
$30 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Starring Brendan Fraser and packed with special effects, ``The  
Mummy'' opening was Universal's third biggest after ``The Lost 
World: Jurrasic Park'' ($90.2 million) and ``Jurassic Park'' ($47 
million). 
</P>
<P>
	Universal chose to brave the heavily-hyped May 19 release of  
``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace'' by positioning ``The 
Mummy'' in the same slot that proved so successful last year for 
``Deep Impact.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Nikki Rocco, Universal president of distribution, said the  
decision was made ``in order to stake our claim for what we knew 
would be the first big event movie for the summer.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Sean Connery adventure ``Entrapment'' dropped to No. 2 with  
a $12.3 million gross in its second week of release. It's earned 
nearly $40 million so far. The Keanu Reeves movie ``The Matrix'' 
was third with $5.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The Reese Witherspoon-Matthew Broderick satire ``Election''  
opened in wide release to place fourth with $3.2 million, ``Never 
Been Kissed'' was fifth with $3 million and ``Analyze This'' was 
sixth with $1.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The Robert DeNiro-Billy Crystal comedy also crossed the $100  
million barrier after 10 weeks of release. 
</P>
<P>
	The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through  
Sunday, followed by distributing studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled by Exhibitor Relations Co. Inc. and 
ACNielsen EDI Inc.: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``The Mummy,'' Universal, $43.4 million, 3,209 locations,  
$13,515 average, $43.4 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``Entrapment,'' 20th Century Fox, $12.3 million, 2,855  
locations, $4,318 average, $38.5 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	3. ``The Matrix,'' Warner Bros., $5.9 million, 2,860 locations,  
$2,056 average, $138.5 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	4. ``Election,'' Paramount, $3.2 million, 827 locations, $3,824  
average, $3.7 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	5. ``Never Been Kissed,'' Fox, $3 million, 2,404 locations,  
$1,250 average, $40.5 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	6. ``Analyze This,'' Warner Bros., $1.7 million, 1,995  
locations, $865 average, $100.8 million, 10 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	7. ``10 Things I Hate About You,'' Disney, $1.1 million, 1,712  
locations, $661 average, $32.6 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	8. ``Life,'' Universal, $1 million, 2,438 locations, $420  
average, $51.5 million, four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	9. ``Cookie's Fortune,'' October, $850,072, 552 locations,  
$1,540 average, $7.7 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	10. ``Shakespeare in Love,'' Miramax, $785,199, 903 locations,  
$870 average, $94 million, 22 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	11. ``The Out-of-Towners,'' Paramount, $777,036, 1,306  
locations, $595 average, $26 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	12. ``Life is Beautiful,'' Miramax, $767,739, 812 locations,  
$945 average, $54.2 million, 29 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	13. ``Idle Hands,'' Sony, $701,678, 1,611 screens, $436 average,  
$3 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	14. ``Pushing Tin,'' Fox, $680,889, 1,160 locations, $587  
average, $7 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	15. ``She's All That,'' Miramax, $625,873, 613 locations, 1,021  
average, $61.6 million, 15 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	16. ``Forces of Nature,'' DreamWorks, $563,188, 1,117 locations,  
$504 average, $50.3 million, eight weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	17. ``Go,'' Sony, $552,220, 884 locations, $625 average, $15.4  
million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	18. ``Lost &AMP; Found,'' Warner Bros., $421,781, 1,284 locations,  
$328 average, $5.8 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	19. ``A Walk on the Moon,'' Miramax, $421,021, 243 locations,  
$1,733 average, $3.1 million, seven weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	20. ``October Sky,'' Universal, $291,660, 429 locations, $680  
average, $30 million, 12 weeks. 
</P>
