<HEADLINE> LSU Coach Bertman Is Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- LSU head baseball coach Skip Bertman has  
been hospitalized for an irregular heartbeat which was detected 
Sunday by doctors after he complained of nausea. 
</P>
<P>
	Bertman's complaint came during the Tigers' plane flight from  
Atlanta, where the team had a three-game series with Georgia. He 
was taken to an area hospital where doctors discovered the 
irregularity and gave him medication to correct it, the university 
said in a written statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Bertman, 61, said doctors have told him there was no structural  
damage to his heart. However, he was ordered to rest and will miss 
Tuesday's game at Northeast Louisiana. Bertman is expected to 
rejoin the team practice Wednesday. 
</P>
