<HEADLINE> Mother's Day Cruise Turns Deadly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOOD RIVER, Ore. (AP) -- One woman was killed and another injured  
Sunday after a loading ramp fell on them during a Mother's Day 
cruise on the Columbia River. 
</P>
<P>
	Coast Guard officials say the Queen of the West cruise ship had  
moored at Hood River when the accident occurred about 11:30 a.m. 
The women, who were together on the cruise, were on the deck below 
when the ramp fell. 
</P>
<P>
	They were taken to a Hood River hospital, where one victim was  
pronounced dead. The other was flown to Portland's Legacy Emanuel 
Hospital. Her condition was not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of the accident is under investigation. The women's  
names and relationship have not been released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
